(174423, '4B2B8462-C02F-476F-A5BC-128172CC7535', 'I’m reading about this cool after school model and this person wrote this description about how she founded the org. Thought it was cool. “Wishbone began in my classroom at Locke High School in South Central, Los Angeles when I was teaching 10th grade English with Teach for America. My students were skipping class, missing assignments, and failing out of school. I realized that my students were struggling to find relevance. Beth Schmidt Printed On: 7 August 2015 The 2015 J.M.K. Innovation Prize 6 I assigned a paper: “Tell me about a passion you have and how you would pursue it.” Students wrote about learning criminal justice at UCLA, film production at Universal Studios and guitar at the Redondo School of Music. I ran a marathon to raise $12,000 and send seven students to the programs they had written about in their papers. Upon return, these students’ attendance rates increased; their GPAs went up, and they claimed that pursuing passions made them realize what could be possible for their lives. Conventionally, we think of educational opportunity as wholly academic, structured and full of resources. I attended a high school that fit this definition, yet even with all of this opportunity, school wasn’t what urged my 16-year old self to be successful. Growing up, I was a competitive figure skater, and this gave me a sense of dedication, purpose and confidence unlike anything else I had experienced. I felt my best out on the ice, and this created self-driven motivation to achieve in everything in my life. I thrived in school because skating taught me the intangible skills we all believe matter for kids to succeed. In the face of darkness and adversity, my Locke students were still motivated by the same things I was at their age. They wanted to feel a sense of purpose and confidence in something like I did in figure skating. Despite the obvious lack of traditional resources at low-income schools, I argue that our students are most starved of the opportunity to pursue passion.”', '460853273000000000', '460853277000000000', 0, 'Nitzan', 'David', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'None', 'nitzan.pelman@gmail.com', '2015-08-09T15:47:53'),
