(174233, 'FF6351A4-A7BD-4199-82FF-3730120E0A86', 'Don''t we all pretend to be strong for most people?  You are strong. But you have allowed yourself to be vulnerable with me and I will reciprocate.   I''m scared too. You''ve forced me rather quickly to reconsider my preconceived notions of the path ahead. Another kid? The commitment, after what I''ve just been through, scares the hell out of me. Scared of letting myself completely dive in with you, not fully trusting myself. The hardest thing for me was being with a strong woman, Marla, and waking up after things got really hard, and realizing I didn''t have a partner...that I was on my own. The thought of having that happen again...with another kid in the mix, is really frightening for me.  You''ve gone straight to my core. I thought maybe this phase was going to be filled with 35 year old yoga instructors, nope. As my witch friend Monyca would say, ''the Shekinah has other plans for you....listen to her.'' So hard to turn off our heads. A wise woman challenged me with a provocation.... ''what if we just fell madly in love?'' I''m learning. We are not in control. ', '460966545000000000', '460970120000000000', 1, 'David', 'Nitzan', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'None', 'David', '2015-08-10T23:15:45'),
(174242, 'C267A5ED-D9E4-432B-95ED-DF335464405E', 'Not often that I can listen to a song I wrote years ago and tear up, but this one just did. I wrote it while in deep despair about not being able to have kids. Had this idea that the babies were in the skies and hanging from the trees waiting for us to be ready. They choose to have us as parents...we don''t choose when we are ready to have kids. Again, we are not in control. I recently re recorded it and sung it into my iPhone. Honestly, I feel a bit reluctant to share. I''m not sure the music is a part of me that resonates with you. Some of these songs are  windows into me on a different level. They are deeply meaningful to me.  ', '460967537000000000', '460970120000000000', 1, 'David', 'Nitzan', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'None', 'David', '2015-08-10T23:32:17'),
